Party Report Compusphere 2005
- --- -------------------------- --- -
µF1µC5 by Scicco/Scarab



µI0075
µC6Smoke as smoke can...

µJEµC0Sweden, a land far away from the little village in Germany I live in. But well, I have that cheap Ryanair Airport Hahn next to my home and as this company offers cheap flights to Gothenburg I decided in time to visit the rebirth of the Compusphere. And let me introduce this party report by saying that is was really worth to visit the party. Now you can read why. :)




µC6Traveling - Drive, Wait, Fly, Wait, Drive, Arrive

µC0The most boring thing if you travel alone. But only until I arrived at the airport. Luckily I had Pezac/Nature in Sweden helping me very much in getting everything running smoth. Esau/Traktor had a van borrowed from his work and he was traveling with four more guys to the party: Malmis/Nature, Pezac/Nature, Zickbone and another one, I forgot his name, sorry! Shame on me.

µC0They catched me at the airport so we drove together to the party place. And this van was not just a van, it was a really cool sceners traveling superb van. It has those really soft leather seats, a TV and a video recorder so we watched demos all the way to the Compusphere. That was actually a really good start and we got into the right mood for party time. It took us less than an hour to arrive.

µC6Party Party Party

µC0We found a really nice place to spend the next days. After building everything up we walked around to inspect the party place. There was a chillout area in the back of the building and the basement was reserved for sleeping only. Nice. Anyway we don't wanted to wait longer so the first beer was opened. Pezac built up his tent and then we started with the barbecue. It was not very warm outside (you know, compared to the Swedes I am a guy from the south, and guys from the south always freeze in the cold north ;) but we had luck as it was not raining. At that time we didn't even knew that the weather will get very perfect the next days.

µC0While waiting for the meat to get ready some Tulou guys arrived. Inside there were even more Amiga guys hacking their machines. It's really a pity that I wasn't able to bring my Amiga with me, but air planes and monitors are things that don't fit very well. Anyway I got my harddisk with me and we connected it on Pezacs Amiga so that we were able to examine some code together. Real scene spirit needs that coding discussions, at least if you are a coder. ;)

µC0While discussion some code Kufa/Scarab arrived, too. Fortunately he managed to show up so I was no longer the only foreigner. Later some Danish guys from Rebels showed up, too, so I hadn't to feel lost in an unknown country. ;)
 

