µC0After changing to fresh clothes and swapping the stinky mouth with brushed teeth I felt better and the compos started. Of course there were some fun entries in all of the graphics categories but there were also some serious pictures which were nice. The music compos had some good entries, too.

µC0Directly after the compos we voted and waited for the price giving. In the meanwhile we packed our things together, you know, the standard actions you perform when the party is near the end. Nothing new here.

µC0The pricegiving was interesting, at least I think this because lot's of people had their fun. I didn't understood anything of course, guess why. ;) But I understood the compo category and the name of the scener who won, that was enough.


µC6RTS, CTRL-X, Alt-F4, File->Quit

µC0Ok, medals given away, now lets pack the van to get back home, sweet home. Kufa joined us this time and we enjoyed one more trip with the van that wins easily all sceners hearts. So, I'm at the airport now, waiting three more hours for my plane to leave and this is where I'm typing this text now. The future is unwrittten, but if your read these lines the plane did not crash and there might be a sequel of the compusphere, the partyreport or the snoring zombie basement storie.

µC0Anyway, come to the next compusphere, it was a really nice party with much Amiga Sceners and true scene spirit! Oh, and let me leave some thanking words to Pezac and Esau for helping me that much in traveling there and of course to all the others I met there for making my days!

µC0The result of another great party: I still love the scene. :)
